Cybersecurity plays a critical role in protecting digital information and systems from attacks, damage, or unauthorized access.

ðŸŽ¯ Main Roles of Cybersecurity:
  Protect Data & Systems
    Keeps sensitive information (like passwords, financial data) safe from hackers.
  Prevent Cyber Attacks
    Stops threats such as viruses, malware, ransomware, and phishing.
  Ensure Business Continuity
    Helps businesses keep running smoothly even during cyber incidents.
  Maintain Privacy
    Ensures personal and organizational data is kept confidential.
  Detect & Respond to Threats
    Identifies cyber threats early and responds quickly to reduce harm.
  Support Legal & Regulatory Compliance
    Helps organizations follow data protection laws (like GDPR, HIPAA).
  Build Trust
    Gives users and customers confidence that their data is secure.
